#Text=AirAsia jet vanishes over Indonesia , 162 missing
#Text=Sunday , December 28 , 2014
#Text=An Indonesia AirAsia jet vanished over the Kumai region today .
#Text=The flight carried 162 people .
#Text=The missing aircraft , photographed in April .
#Text=Image : Oka Sudiatmika .
#Text=Among the 155 passengers and seven crew flying from Surabaya to Singapore are three Koreans , one Malaysian , and one person variously reported as a French or UK national .
#Text=The rest are Indonesians .
#Text=There are sixteen children and an infant .
#Text=The plane was diverting around weather formations over the Java Sea when contact with air traffic control ( ATC ) in Jakarta was lost .
#Text=Local search and rescue have been told the flight last spoke to controllers at 6:12 local time seeking to climb from 32,000 ft to 38,000ft .
#Text=The flight vanished from radar at 6:17 .
#Text=The transponder ceased to be received a minute later .
#Text=ATC issued a series of escalating alerts in response .
#Text=It was due to enter Singaporean airspace at 6:52 and land by around 8:30 .
#Text=The Indonesian Navy , police forces , and National Search and Rescue Agency are focusing on an area 20 nautical miles from East Belitung .
#Text=The plane went missing in the vicinity of Pulau Belitung Island .
#Text=A rescue boat with a crew of 22 has been dispatched , with water police providing an additional vessel .
#Text=The Indonesian Civil Aviation Authority is overseeing the efforts .
#Text=Searches are presently suspended until morning .
#Text=The flight path of the missing flight .
#Text=Image : Andrew Heneen /Natural Earth .
#Text=The Civil Aviation Authority of Singapore is " ready to provide any assistance to support the search and rescue effort " according to a statement .
#Text=The Singaporean military has sent two C-130 aircraft to assist .
#Text=The Indian Navy has reportedly placed three ships and a Boeing P8-1 on standby to help .
#Text=Australia has also offered assistance .
#Text=Australian Foreign Minister Julie Bishop telephoned her Indonesian equivalent , Retno Marsudi , to offer support .
#Text=Bishop has also offered Australian assistance to South Korea , Singapore , and Malaysia .
#Text=Australian Prime Minister Tony Abbott contacted Indonesian President Joko Widodo to offer sympathies and a P3 Orion plane .
#Text=Areas for families and friends have been set up at Changi Airport where the flight was headed and at Juanda International Airport where it departed .
#Text=The airline said in a statement they would " keep all parties informed as more information becomes available " about " the status of the passengers and crew members on board " .
#Text=" I hope I can get information soon on the whereabouts of our family members , " one weeping woman at Juanda told Antara .
#Text=She said she has four relatives on board and heard about the disappearance from news reports .
#Text=The area where the plane vanished around 40 minutes into its trip was experiencing thunderstorms .
#Text=Some clouds were as high as 50,000ft .
#Text=The aircraft , Airbus A320-200 registration PK-AXC and serial number 3648 , was six years old .
#Text=It was undertaking flight designation QZ8501 and last underwent maintenance in November .
#Text=Management company Doric own and lease the aircraft .
#Text=I hope I can get information soon on the whereabouts of our family members — Woman awaiting news at Juanda Airport
#Text=Pilot Iriyanto and co-pilot Remi Emmanuel Plesel have over 8,000 hours experience between them .
#Text=Airbus released a statement saying the plane had accumulated 23,000 flying hours on 13,600 flights .
#Text=The French-based airframer said it would assist investigators .
#Text=The BEA , which investigates aviation mishaps in France , is liaising with their Indonesian counterparts at the National Transportation Safety Committee to provide assistance .
#Text=The engines were built by CFM International , a joint enterprise between US firm General Electric and French engineering company Safran .
#Text=The US connection means the US National Transportation Safety Board ( NTSB ) can also join the probe .
#Text=The NTSB says it is ready and willing to assist if required .
#Text=Our priority is looking after all the next-of-kin for my staff and passengers — AirAsia owner Tony Fernandes
#Text=A screenshot apparently leaked from an ATC radar screen shows the flight ascending through 36,000ft with a ground speed of 353 knts .
#Text=The aircraft would normally be travelling faster , with an Emirates jet also on the screen showing a ground speed of 503knts at 36,000ft .
#Text=" My only thought are with the passengers and my crew " said AirAsia boss Tony Fernandes .
#Text=He said he is heading to Surabaya and thanked Malaysian , Singaporean , and Indonesian authorities for emergency efforts .
#Text=Fernandes bought AirAsia for a symbolic price from the Malaysian government in 2002 .
#Text=By 2010 it had expanded from two aircraft to 86 .

#Text=Pope Francis used today 's address in St. Peter 's Square , the Vatican to say he was praying for the missing .
